 JOB DESCRIPTION
 Develop and manage new Regional SIP service to complement domestic SIP Trunking serives to complete Singtel SIP Trunking offer to customers in Singapore with regional presence, strengthening the proposition of SIP Trunking in defending legacy ISDN services, maintaining leadership in this Voice trunk market.Manage new government WAN project, develop process and manage project P&LDevelop product features, pricing plan, and business processes for new services. Work with Engineering, IS and Operations on the development of new servicesIdentify target market and product positioning of new servicesDevelop product strategies and manage product life cycleDevelop product costing with Finance and maintain an updated set of product costing.  Continuously review product processes and cost components to reduce product costing and increase product profitabilityEnsure continuous process review and improvement to enhance customer experience, operational efficiency as well as reduce cost.Monitor and ensure that revenue and profitability targets of the product are met.  Detect any negative trends, investigate and explain any anomalies in revenue or costing trends and propose solutions to correct itEnhance product features and review pricing to ensure product competitiveness and service quality based on benchmarks/feedbacksEnsure availability and timeliness of product information to internal stakeholders as well as provide product training to various stakeholders.Analyze market and competitive information to identify market needs and corresponding product enhancements / development requiredDevelop product policies and ensure regulatory complianceEngage customer for better understanding of market demand and sensingEngage sales and segments to gain mindshare and drive towards product revenue/drivers targetsThe idea candidate should possess: Degree in Engineering, Business Administration or MarketingPreferably with 2-3 years of Product Management / Product Marketing experienceKnowledge of SIP/VOIP, layer 3 WAN connectivity, internet & telecommunications industry.  Technical knowledge in Layer 3 Services would be advantageous.Keen sense of technology developments, market trends, and needs of the data communications market.Achievement and customer oriented.Creative and with drive. 


 



