Product Manager (Carrier Ethernet)

Singapore Telecommunications Limited












			Min 7 years (Manager) 
		








			Singapore - Central		















 JOB DESCRIPTION
 Responsibilities• Responsible for managing C+ IPLC (International Private Leased Circuit), C+ E-Line and the development of new International Carrier Ethernet products• Develop and manage product portfolio to meet the needs of existing and new customer segments.• Plan and develop new products/features to ensure product relevance and meet changing market needs.• Manage cost structure (internal & external), product profitability and customer value.• Regularly monitors product quality against target levels and trigger corrective action where necessary.• Understand market needs; keep abreast of technology developments/trends and competitive situation.• Monitor and analyse product performance as well as manage product life cycle to maximize revenue and profitable market share.• Work with Marketing team to develop product strategies and determine market segmenting, targeting and positioning.• Work with Information Systems (IS) and Billing Systems (BS) teams to support product requirements.• Develop product policies and ensure consistency of execution internally and externally.• Analyse product requirement for major submarine cable projects and make recommendation to Management on cable investment decisions. The interested applicant should possess:• Degree in Engineering, Business Administration or Marketing, minimal 3 years of Product Management / Product Development experience in telecommunications industry.• Good written and oral communications skills.• Knowledge of telecommunications industry, sound technical knowledge in Carrier Ethernet and IPLC Services will be an added advantage.• Keen sense of technology developments, market trends, and needs of the data communications market.• Achievement and customer oriented. Independent, creative and with drive.• Have the drive, energy and commitment to succeed in winning in a competitive market environment.  


 



